          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1615218102245-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix </strong>in 200ml [300ml] <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>– this is your <strong>beef stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1615218106805-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1615218106805-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1615218106805-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1615218106805-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
